criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  individuals aged 18 to 29 years of both sexes with chroma greater than A2 in the upper
             incisors and canines, in the Vita Classical color scale;

          -  absence of active caries lesions

          -  patients who had never undergone bleaching therapy;

          -  good oral hygiene and no hypersensitivity to tactile and evaporative stimuli through
             the Visual Analog Pain Scale;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  patients undergoing fixed orthodontic treatment;

          -  patients with darkened non-vital teeth and/or with extensive restorations in molars;

          -  presence of cracks or fractures;

          -  patients allergic to the product, with the presence of gastroesophageal disorders and
             with dentinal exposure in anterior and/or posterior teeth.
